{
  "texts": [
    "Deep RL, which goes one step farther, has enormous potential for both deepfake detection and defending against antiforensic assaults on the detectors.",
    "Since RL can simulate an autonomous agent to perform consecutive actions ideally with little to no prior understanding of the environment, it might be applied to the development of algorithms to identify anti-forensic processing and the creation of deepfake attack detectors.",
    "A review of deep RL approaches developed for solving cyber-security problems can be found in Nguyen et al. (2019), including autonomous intrusion detection techniques and multiagent game theory simulations for defense strategies.",
    "Due to the increasing number of data sources, frequency, type and volume, a centralized system handling all this input may not be an optimal solution regarding scalability and efficiency.",
    "The Edge Computing paradigm tries to solve this by virtualizing network functions and deploying them at the network edge (Shi and Dustdar 2016)."
  ]
}